Package executor.service

Class App

java.lang.Object
executor.service.App
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.springframework.boot.CommandLineRunner
@EnableJpaAuditing @SpringBootApplication public class App extends Object implements org.springframework.boot.CommandLineRunner
Main class for the Spring Boot application.

This class is the entry point for the Spring Boot application. It is annotated with @SpringBootApplication, indicating that it is the primary configuration class and enabling auto-configuration of the Spring context. Additionally, it is annotated with @EnableJpaAuditing, enabling JPA entity auditing features such as automatic population of auditing fields like createdBy, createdDate, etc.

Implements CommandLineRunner to provide a callback for executing custom logic when the application is fully started. This allows for additional setup or initialization tasks to be performed at application startup.

  • Constructor Details

    • App

      public App(ParallelFlowExecutorService executorService)
      Constructor for the App class.

      Initializes an instance of the App class with a provided ParallelFlowExecutorService. This constructor is typically used for dependency injection, allowing the injection of a pre-configured instance of the parallel flow executor service into the application.

      The parallel flow executor service is responsible for managing and executing parallel flows or tasks within the application. It allows for efficient concurrent execution of tasks, enhancing performance in scenarios where parallelism is beneficial.

      Parameters:
      executorService - The ParallelFlowExecutorService responsible for managing parallel flows or tasks within the application.

      The main entry point of the application.

      Uses SpringApplication.run(Class, String...) to start the Spring Boot application. This method initializes the Spring context, applies auto-configuration, and starts the embedded web server if applicable.

      The App class is specified as the primary configuration class, and any command line arguments provided are passed to the application.

    • run

      public void run(String... args)
      Callback method used to run the application after the Spring context is loaded.

      This method is part of the CommandLineRunner interface and is invoked after the application context is fully loaded and before the Spring Boot application starts. It provides a convenient way to execute custom logic at application startup.

      In this implementation, the method delegates the execution to the injected ParallelFlowExecutorService by invoking its execute method. This allows for the initiation of parallel flows or tasks within the application.

      Specified by:
      run in interface org.springframework.boot.CommandLineRunner
      Parameters:
      args - Command line arguments passed to the application.
